25/07/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- US Deputy Assistant Secretary for European and Eurasian Affairs Rosemary A. DiCarlo says President George W. Bush is considering Montenegro's request to establish diplomatic ties.
In a statement broadcast Monday (24 July) on Montenegrin TV, DiCarlo said a decision is expected within weeks.
In a separate statement Monday, Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov said that Moscow expects Montenegro to be a factor of stability in the region.
Russia decided to launch bilateral diplomatic relations with Montenegro a month ago.
(Pobjeda, Vijesti - 25/07/06)
